[x] read apply_sync's write ordering/locking before touching action-mirror sync $Prerequisite for the action-mirror VTODO swap (learn to import VTODO). apply_sync's doc comment says ordering is load-bearing - TakeAction/TakeCalendar/Converged each stage .actions + sidecar writes differently via PendingBatch. Need to actually trace this before changing what read_ics_dates reads, since a mis-sequenced change here can silently clear a real scheduled_at (mistaking 'can't find the old format' for 'calendar deleted the event'). See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ %2026-07-13T22:48 #019f5a22-7252-7c22-8e66-96aae8692720
[x] decouple sync state from the domain model $The merge base B is a property of the sync pair, not the action. Move it to a sync-owned gitignored store (.clearhead/sync/<pair>.json, action-uuid -> field -> value): plan_sync takes a base_map param symmetric with ics_dates; scheduled_at_sync/due_date_sync come OFF Action and ActionMeta (merge_action/hydrate_actions_map shrink); apply_sync stamps B into the store; one-time seed migration reads existing sidecar _sync values in. Lands BEFORE the action-mirror VTODO swap. See README design notes 2026-07-14.$ !1 %2026-07-17T23:24 #019f5f76-c52c-7020-8dbc-c0f393cf196e
[x] align sync state with the configured plans vdir $Correct the initial decoupling: vdir is the integration boundary. Replace per-pair/caldav state with one clean merge-base store for the configured plan path; remove pair/remote/CalDAV concepts and delete all legacy sidecar migration code. Missing state gets first-sync semantics.$ !1 %2026-07-17T23:45 #019f73f2-7229-7362-83f1-a095084c1761
[x] learn to export things to VTODO format $Plans already emit VTODO+RRULE. Finish the standalone Action half by replacing action_to_vevent with action_to_vtodo. RRULE remains exclusively Plan semantics and never returns to the .actions DSL; recurring capture should write a Plan VTODO directly, then expansion materializes executable Action instances.$ %2026-07-23T00:03 #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3a974ca12f85
